porting circulation, recovery, and overall comfort.<\/p><p>With just <strong>10–15 minutes a day<\/strong>, many dogs relax during treatment and show noticeable improvements in flexibility and wellbeing—all from the comfort of home.<\/p>","text_style":"body"}}},"block_order":["heading_xagcMD","text_Fd6PWW"],"name":"t:sections.image-with-text.presets.name","settings":{"display_id":false,"visibility":"always-display","image":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/4cf891d8-2ca6-43fb-8da3-ab563d0b0060.png","video_autoplay":true,"video_loop":true,"height":"adapt","color_scheme":"background-1","section_color_scheme":"background-1","full_desktop_width":false,"content_layout":"no-overlap","desktop_media_width":50,"layout":"image_first","desktop_content_position":"top","desktop_content_alignment":"left","mobile_full_media_width":false,"mobile_direction":"normal","mobile_image_quanlity":"2","mobile_content_alignment":"left","mobile_padding_top":0,"mobile_padding_bottom":16,"desktop_padding_top":36,"desktop_padding_bottom":36,"custom_colors_background":"#2e2a39","custom_gradient_background":"","custom_colors_text":"#ffffff","custom_colors_solid_button_background":"#dd1d1d","custom_colors_solid_button_text":"#ffffff","custom_colors_outline_button":"#dd1d1d","custom_section_colors_background":"#ffffff","custom_section_gradient_background":""}},"section_divider_j8T7hJ":{"type":"section-divider","name":"Section divider","settings":{"visibility":"always-display","shape":"waves_3","flip_horizontal":false,"flip_vertical":false,"shape_color":"accent-1","custom_shape_color":"#dd1d1d","background_color":"background-1","custom_background_color":"#ffffff","padding_top":0,"padding_bottom":0}},"collapsible_content_paWCPd":{"type":"collapsible-content","blocks":{"collapsible_row_QdNWpa":{"type":"collapsible_row","settings":{"heading":"How often should I use it?","icon":"help","filled_icon":false,"row_content":"<p>Use red light therapy 5–10 minutes daily for acute issues, or 2–3 times per week for chronic conditions. Follow device instructions and consult your vet.<\/p>","page":""}},"collapsible_row_LMkPr9":{"type":"collapsible_row","settings":{"heading":"Is it safe for all pets?","icon":"help","filled_icon":false,"row_content":"<p>Yes! It’s completely safe, non-invasive, and drug-free. It simply uses light—no heat, no pain, no side effects.<\/p>","page":""}},"collapsible_row_ta6mLN":{"type":"collapsible_row","settings":{"heading":"Can I use it while my pet sleeps?","icon":"help","filled_icon":false,"row_content":"<p>Absolutely! The mat can be used while your pet is resting for optimal comfort and healing. Most pets find it relaxing, like a gentle warming sensation.<br\/><br\/><\/p>","page":""}},"collapsible_row_YJeAwc":{"type":"collapsible_row","settings":{"heading":"How long before I see results?","icon":"help","filled_icon":false,"row_content":"<p>Many pet owners see relief after just a few sessions, while others (especially with chronic issues) may take a couple of weeks of consistent use.<br\/><br\/><\/p>","page":""}},"collapsible_row_DTcngF":{"type":"collapsible_row","settings":{"heading":"What conditions can it help with?","icon":"help","filled_icon":false,"row_content":"<ul><li>Arthritis & joint pain<br\/><\/li><li>Muscle soreness<br\/><\/li><li>Injuries & wounds<br\/><\/li><li>Post-surgery recovery<br\/><\/li><li>Stiffness & inflammation<br\/><\/li><\/ul>","page":""}}},"block_order":["collapsible_row_QdNWpa","collapsible_row_LMkPr9","collapsible_row_ta6mLN","collapsible_row_YJeAwc","collapsible_row_DTcngF"],"name":"t:sections.collapsible_content.presets.name","settings":{"display_id":false,"visibility":"always-display","caption":"LEARN MORE","title":"Frequently Asked Questions","title_highlight_color":"#6d388b","heading_size":"h1","heading_alignment":"center","layout":"none","color_scheme":"accent-1","container_color_scheme":"background-2","open_first_collapsible_row":false,"video_muted_autoplay":true,"image_ratio":"adapt","desktop_layout":"image_second","r